Purpose: Demonstrates the end-to-end intelligence model. Sallie can sense her environment through vision, touch, hearing, and smell can navigate around obstacles she sees and move toward goals. Things to try: Move and turn Sallie by using the controls at the upper left of the network. These are akin to the motor controls on a robot. Rotate Sallie a full turn and see how object are mapped into her internal mental model. Notice that it is not terribly accurate as binocular depth perception had decreasing accuracy as the distance increases. Notice as Sallie approaches an obstacle, her perception of it position becomes progressively more accurate until she can touch it for the most accurate possible location information. Enable learning by firing the "Color" neuron. This enables the simulator to say "This is [color]" based on the color direction in front of Sallie. Over time, Sallie can learn the names for colors. Enable more learning by firing the "Action" neuron. The enables the simulator to send commands into Sallie's hearing stream and reward her when she responds correctly. Over time she can learn to Go, Stop, Turn Right, Turn Left, and Say the color in front of her. Current state of development:
